content: I didn't harvest a deer, but I did see some fresh buck rubs near my tree stand, which got me excited for the upcoming rifle season. I spent two days in the stand, but unfortunately, I didn't see any deer within range. The trip was still great, though - I got to spend some quality time with my parents at their cabin on the property and helped my dad with some chores around the property, like fixing a broken fence post and splitting firewood.
